title: Rails and Spartans Go the Distance, Hawks Soar
text:
Rails and Spartans Go the Distance, Hawks Soar 
By Norman Seawright III October 1, 2015 Updated Oct 1, 2015 at 10:38 PM CDT 
(NNCNOW.com) -- In high school volleyball, Proctor and Superior played a full five game match, while Hermantown pulled away from Ashland to add to its winning streak. 
After Hermantown won game one behind Ellie Gamradt's kill, the Oredockers rallied to force the Hawks to play four games. In the end, the Hawks defeated Ashland 4-1, extending the winning streak to 12. The Oredockers will participate in an invitational at Duluth East on October 3, while the Hawks play at Proctor on October 7 at 7:00 PM.
